eminist approaches, art, storytelling, and business. The book also includes reproductions of Susan’s mental health records and dream paintings. This book will be important for consumers of mental health care wishing to understand the conventional system and develop the best quality of life. Rich personal detail, critical perspective, clinical records, and art reproductions make the book engaging for a general audience and stimulating as a teaching resource in nursing, social work, psychology, psychiatry, and art therapy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt therapy. 0aArtistsxBiographyxCanada. 0aArtistszCanadavBiography. 0aMental illnessxTreatment. 0aMentally illxBiographyxCanada. 0aMentally illzCanadavBiography. 0aNarrative therapy. 0aPsychologistsxBiographyxCanada. 0aPsychologistszCanadavBiography. 4aPsychology. 4aSocial Science: Women’s Studies. 7aMEDICAL / Mental Health.2bisacsh1 aBarnes, Rosemary, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458130640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554581306423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554581306/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles